Pairs

Implicit Parameters
. dont' have to be explicitly passed to function
. compiler figures out right parameter to pass

If implicit parameter of type T
. has type compatible with T
. is visible at point of the function call or definied in companion object associated with T

If compiler can find _one_ definition it works, otherwise returns compiler error


val xs = List(0,1,2,3,4,5)
( xs foldLeft 0) ( _ + _ )
( xs foldRight 0) ( _ + _ )


 xs reduceRight ( _ - _ )
 xs reduceLeft ( _ - _ )

